At least four killed in post office shooting 
A gunman killed at least four people in a post office in this wealthy
suburb of New York late Tuesday, police said.
Four or five people were killed, according to an early police tally.
Another man was in critical condition after being shot in the head,
according to the University Hospital in Newark.
The gunman was armed with a nine millimeter pistol and escaped after
the shooting at the Watchung Plaza shopping district, a New York
television station reported.
